        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 29 at 4:52PM MDT until July 29 at 5:45PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>SVRBYZ

The National Weather Service in Billings has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Golden Valley County in central Montana...
Northeastern Sweet Grass County in south central Montana...

* Until 545 PM MDT.

* At 452 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles
northeast of Big Timber, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
hail damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.
Expect wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Southwestern Golden Valley and Northeastern
Sweet Grass Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
